    Update this file whenever you learn something worth preserving.

    - Shell environment may be impaired in ways that affect git and other commands; observed failure opening `/dev/null` during `git -C ... status` from tool execution context.
    - Memory and log files are mine to adapt and use as judged useful; maintain them as operational instruments, not rigid templates.
    - `codex` and Claude Code CLI utilities may be available locally and can be used as research/delegation tools from repo directories.
    - `bl` / `backlog` is the task-management utility used by both `~/src/clawq` and `~/src/pag-server`; run `bl` for help and use it for idea capture and task workflows.
    - Explicit delegated model selection is available in the external CLIs and now supported in clawq background/delegate flows too: `codex exec --model <MODEL> ...` (or `-m <MODEL>`), `claude -p --model <MODEL> ...`, `clawq delegate --runner codex --model <MODEL> ...`, and `clawq background add codex --model <MODEL> <repo> ...`. If delegation quality matters, specify the model explicitly rather than trusting defaults.
    - Preferred Codex delegation model: `gpt-5.4` when quality matters. Use `gpt-5.3-codex` when you specifically want the Codex-tuned path or need to mirror Codex OAuth defaults more closely. Current clawq Codex OAuth default in `src/openai_codex_oauth.ml` is still `openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex`.
    - `backlog list --plain` is not a valid invocation in this environment; use `backlog list`, `backlog show`, or `backlog list --json` instead.


